You would enter 0 for Monday ( they will get meals in school) , 2 for Tuesday, 0 for Wednesday (they will get meals in school), 2 for Thursday and 2 for Friday.

post_text:
Do you know a Student Artist?

The Fenton Arts Council and the Cause & Affect Gallery are collaborating to bring a NEW 3-part ART exhibit to downtown Fenton. We are currently looking for images of student artwork to be in the virtual part of the professional exhibit. Any local student in grades Pre-K through High School is eligible to participate. Simply take a picture of the art piece and submit it through the link below. It's Easy!

Here are a few tips:
Phone photos are fine.
Try placing the art on a dark background for the photo.
Take a few photos of the same art, using different lights, and choose the best to send.
Try to have the camera, or camera phone, shoot the piece straight-on, not at an angle.
If you can, try shooting outside, in the shade.

The exhibit opens July l0, so we need lots of student art in time to put the images into a virtual sideshow.

Click here to submit photo of student art:

https://bit.ly/FACShowcase

post_text:
Due to the Covid-19 pandemic, many of our families may have experienced a change in income. You may still fill out an application to apply for free and reduced meals for this school year online at www.lunchapp.com.
If your family qualifies, these benefits will carry over 30 days into the 2020-2021 school year. This may also make you eligible for additional benefits from the state during this pandemic.
If you have any questions, please email our Food Service Director, Anna Goss at agoss@lakefentonschools.org.

This past summer, nearly 400 high school students secured jobs in Genesee County through the Summer Youth Initiative. One thing they all had in common? They were all graduates of the @TeenQuestFGCC pre-employment training program.
Prepare for your next (or first!) job by signing up for TeenQuest’s next session, which runs Feb. 24 through March 26 at Lake Fenton High School. The program will be held Monday through Thursday from 2:45-4:45 p.m. each day. #LFLeads
https://bit.ly/2SGsGk3

post_text:
Our first ever LF Book Bus made its rounds both on Channel 12 news today and throughout our school community. Hundreds of books were handed out to kids across the district!
A huge thank you to Principal Shaughnessy and Principal Conover for their hard work! Another big thank you to First Student transportation, United Way Project READ! Staff, and Fenton’s Open Book for donating time and books to this great event. And thank YOU LF Community for the book donations and welcoming smiles all day long!
Next year already plans to be bigger and better! #LFLeads 📚 💙

The Genesee County Metropolitan Planning Commission is conducting a study assessing the health and economic impacts of active living and the facilities that support this lifestyle. GCMPC is interested in learning more about residents active living participation and spending habits associated with aerobic activity (walking, running, biking, etc). The survey should take no more than 5 minutes. All your responses will be anonymous. Thank you for your help!
https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/TrailBenefits
